<section class="article-body">
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 18pt; color: #0000ff;"><strong>Book sale</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Don't miss our&nbsp; book sale on&nbsp; Saturday May 7. Fill a bag with books of your choice for only $2.00 !</span></strong></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 18pt; color: #0000ff;"><strong>Vernissage</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 39.45pt 0.0001pt 30px;"><strong><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 14pt;"></span><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Louise Kelly explores the evening light in Huntingdon at the Little Green Library. Join us and meet the artist at the vernissage on Saturday May 7, from 2 to 4 p.m.</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="color: #000000;"></span></span></strong></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 39.45pt 0.0001pt 30px;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">For her, this town has a special vibration. Her collection of oil paintings on wood, created over the past few months, captures this special aura.</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="color: #000000;"></span></span></strong></p>
<p style="margin: 0cm 39.45pt 0.0001pt 30px;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">A teacher at &eacute;cole Arthur-Pigeon for 25 years, since 2014, the artist now pursues her artistic path full time.&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;<img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/images/ArtExhibit/LK1s.jpg" alt="LK1s" /></span></span></strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;<img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/images/ArtExhibit/LK2s.jpg" alt="LK2s" /></p>
<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/images/ArtExhibit/LK3s.jpg" alt="LK3s" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p> </section>


